1. What is file upload in selenium?
- File upload means sending a file from your system to web application using selenium

2. How to do you upload a file in selenium?
- Use send_keys() on <input type="file">

    file_input.send_keys(file_path)

3. Why do we use send_keys() for file upload?
- Because Selenium directly sets the file path to the input element without opening os popup

4. Do we need to click "Browse" button in selenium?
- NO
- Selenium bypasses it using send_keys()

5. Can selenium handle OS file upload popup?
- NO
- Selenium works only with browser elements, not OS windows.

6. What kind of file path shoud be used?
- Absolute path
- Example: C:\Users\test\file.txt

7. What happens if you given wrong file path?
- InValidArgumentException

8. Can we upload multiple files?
- YES
- input_element.send_keys("file1.xtx\nfile2.txt")

9. How do you verify file upload success?
- Check:
    - Success message
    - upload file name displayed
    - Status change

10. What type of element is used for file upload?
- <input type="file">

11. What if <input type="file"> is hidden?
- Use javascript to make it visible

    driver.execute_script("argument[0].style.display='block';",element)

12. What if application uses custom upload button?
- Check if hidden <input type="file"> exists in DOM
- If yes -> use send_keys()
- If no -> use external tools (AutoIT/PyAutoGUI)

13. Difference between standard and non-standard upload?
Type & Description & Handling
-----------------------------
- Standard , <input type="file"> , send_keys
- Non-standard , OS popup  , AutoIT/PyAutoGUI

14. Why is Selenium not able to handle file popup?
- Because Popup belongs to operating system, not browser DOM

15. How do you upload file using project folder path?
    import os
    file_path=os.path.abspath("testdata/file.txt")

16. What is best practice for file upload?
- Store files in object
- Use relative -> Convert to absolute path
- Avoid hardcoding paths

17. How do you handle drag-and-drop upload?
- Use:
    - Javascript executor OR
    - ActionChains(limited support)

18. What exception occurs if element is hidden?
- ElementNotInteractableException

19. Can we upload file in headless mode?
- YES
- Works same as norman browser

20. What are real-time challenges in file upload?
- Hidden elements
- Dynamic locators
- Custom UI (no input tag)
- Timing issue
- Large file uploads

21. How do you handle file upload popup?
- Answer
    -> Selenium cannot handle OS-level popups directly because they are not part of the browser DOM
- So we handle it 2 ways:
    - CASE - 1: if <input file="file"> is present
        - Use send_keys() directly (No popup handling needed)
    - CASE - 2: If OS popup appears
        - AutoIT (Windows)
        - PyAutoGUI (Python)
        - Robot Class
👉 Interview Line:
    If the file upload is standard , I use send_keys(). It it triggers an OS popup , i handle it using tools like AutoIT or PyAutoGUI

22. Difference between send_keys() and AutoIT?
Feature & send_keys() & AutoIT
------------------------------
- Works on -> Browser DOM , OS windows
- speed -> Fast , Slower
- Reliability -> High , medium
- Dependency -> No external tool , Requires installation
- Use case -> <input type="file"> , File upload popup

👉 Interview Line:
    send_keys() is preferred because , it's fast and directly interact with DOM. AutoIT is used only when OS-level popup appears

24. What if <input type="file"> is hidden?
- If the element is hidden, selenium cannnot interact with it directly
- Solution:
    Use Javascript to make it visible:
        driver.execute_script("argument[0].style.display="block;",element)
        element.send_keys("C:\\file.txt")
👉 Alternative:
    Sometimes even if hidden , send_keys() still works without making visible

👉 Interview Line:
    If the file input is hidden, I use Javascript to make it visible or directly try send_keys if supported.

25. Can Selenium upload multiple files?
- YES, Selenium can upload multiple files only if the input has multiple attribute
    <input type="file" multiple>
    file_input.send_keys("C:\\file1.txt\nC:\\file2.txt")

26. Why Selenium cannot handle OS popup?
- Selenium works with only web elements inside the browser (DOM)
- File upload popup:
    - Belongs to OS
    - Not part of HTML/DOM
    - Selenium has no control over OS-level UI

👉 Interview Line:
    Selenium can not handle OS level popups because , it interacts only with browser DOM , while file upload popups belongs to the OS .
